{"name":"Drugs Of Abuse","id":15,"content":"<h2>Marijuana</h2>\n\n<p>Marijuana&mdash;also called&nbsp;<em>weed, herb, pot, grass, bud, ganja, Mary Jane</em>, and a vast number of other slang terms&mdash;is a greenish-gray mixture of the dried&nbsp;flowers of&nbsp;<em>Cannabis sativa.</em>&nbsp;Consumed in form of Joint, Bong, Blunt, or mixed with edibles. Main Chemical that alters mind:&nbsp;<em>delta-9-tetrahydrocannabinol</em>&nbsp;(THC).</p>\n\n<p>Effects:&nbsp;pleasant euphoria and sense of relaxation (some instead experience anxiety, fear, distrust, or panic <em>maybe it depends on brain conditions of a particular person at the particular time</em>),&nbsp;heightened sensory perception (e.g., brighter colors), laughter, altered perception of time, and increased appetite (degree of effects varies among people as is the case with any other drug). Fear, Hallucinations, Delusions have also been seen in case of high dosage.</p>\n\n<p>Eating or drinking marijuana delivers significantly less THC into the bloodstream than smoking an equivalent amount of the plant.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://d14rmgtrwzf5a.cloudfront.net/sites/default/files/images/colorbox/brain2.jpg\" style=\"width: 781px; height: 503px;\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Addiction:</strong>&nbsp;In simple words, 30% of consumers have shown marijuana use disorder which can convert into Addiction if the consumer cannot stop using the drug even after seeing an effect on many aspects in life.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n","authorId":null,"subject":"science","tags":[""],"img":null,"summary":null,"lastUpdated":null}